th Family and Healthcare Providers\n\n•  Share weekly updates with family members.\n•  Consult healthcare providers as needed to adjust care strategies.\n\n8. Review and Adapt the Care Plan as Needed\n\n•  Conduct monthly care reviews to assess Karen’s health and cognitive function.\n•  Modify the care plan as Karen’s needs evolve.\n\n\x0cPersonalized Engagement Program for Karen\n\nThis engagement plan is designed to support Karen’s cognitive function, emotional well-\nbeing, and independence while aligning with her interests and personality.\n\nActivities Tailored to Karen’s Interests\n\n1. Television & Storytelling\n\n•  TV viewing will be altered to remove soaps, which caused stress. Karen will now\nwatch lighter content like comedies, old musicals, animal-related shows, and\nfamily movies.', 'Dexterity exercises, music, Casey time\n\nAfternoon (2:00 - 4:00 PM) TV shows, reminiscence therapy, social engagement\n\nEvening (6:00 - 8:00 PM)\n\nLight conversation, reading, relaxation\n\nFinal Notes\n\nThis  integrated  care  and  engagement  plan  ensures  that  Karen  receives  consistent,\ncompassionate,  and  stimulating  care  while  maintaining  her  independence  and  dignity.\nAdjustments will be made as needed based on her evolving needs, preferences, and well-\nbeing.\n\nThank  you  for  your  involvement  in  Karen’s  care.  Please  feel  free  to  reach  out  with  any\nquestions or concerns.\n\n\x0cT I M E\n\nS U N D A Y\n\nM O N D A Y\n\nT U E S D A Y\n\nW E D N E S D A Y\n\nT H U R S D A Y\n\nF R I D A Y\n\nS A T U R D A Y\n\nM O R N I N G\n( 8 : 0 0   A M   -\n1 2 : 0 0   P M )\n\nWake-up &\nHygiene:\nBreakfast &\nhydration\nMobility\nexercises\n(stretching)\nSquish ball\nEngagement:\nReminiscence\ntherapy (photo\nviewing)']
